    "Indeed, set S:= Ric gB -h * g sym, s:= tr gB S. From the local computations in [Mül12, Thm.",
    "4.5] we have that the evolution of s along harmonic Ricci flow is∂ t s = ∆s + 2 ∥ S∥ 2 + 2 ∥τ gB (h)∥ 2.On the other hand, given (34) it follows that the solution is self-similar, thus∂ t s = X H (s) -s,where X H is the lift of ∇f to B.",
    "Since s is π 1 (B)-invariant, it induces a smooth function s: B → R, which by the above satisfies ∆s -⟨∇s, ∇f ⟩ + 2 ∥S∥ 2 + 2 ∥τ gB (h)∥ 2 + s = 0.",
    "At this point one may argue exactly as in the Ricci flow case, see e.g.",
    "the proof of [CCG + 07, Prop."
